The players that will miss Wednesday’s (today) Premier League clash between Manchester United and West Ham United have been revealed. According to a post on Man United’s official website, the likes of Luke Shaw, Axel Tuanzebe and Phil Jones will not feature for the host against West Ham at Old Trafford due to injuries. Shaw, Tuanzebe and Jones also missed Man United’s FA Cup semi-final defeat against Chelsea on Sunday. The visitors, West Ham, will be without Robert Snodgrass and Ryan Fredericks due to injuries. Man United are currently in the 5th position on the Premier League table with 62 points after 36 games. West Ham, on the other hand, are in 16th position on the log with 37 points after 36 matches. The match kick-off time is scheduled for 6 pm.